It’s not a huge deal bc probably 99.9% unlikely you both carry it.  But it’s the ATM gene , I am a carrier.  

It’s easy for you two to get genetic testing to see if any possible issues with future kids.  

Nevan and I didn’t do it until I was pregnant .. but it’s better to do ahead of time

If you AND Melissa are both carriers of the ATM gene then you’d want to make embryos and test them for ATM.. you wouldn’t want to have kids the old fashion way. 

But really unlikely that you are both carriers.
Ok good intel I’ll share with Melissa. Thank for telling us
This is the very rare disease that can result if both parents carry ATM..
https://medlineplus.gov/genetics/condition/ataxia-telangiectasia/
It’s awful .. but luckily very rare
And luckily we can test for it ahead of making babies!
